result.formatted_address: Hong Kong, Chuk Un, Ching Tak St, 136號130
result.name: Itamomo Cafe

reviews.text: Food was decent, service was decent and portions were pretty filling but nothing too special. Toast was a bit too dry. Afternoon tea was a lot better, the food had good flavours and the portions were pretty big.

Super cheap and big portions! Seating is really spacious for Hong Kong, classy setting for a budget, staff are nice but it gets a little busy during dinner so try and get there earlier so you dont have to line
I always enjoy having breakfast at Itamomo, because of the quality and price.

Good quality for the price. Went in a group of 3, ordered 3 dinner set (main + soup + drink), and 2 sides, it was 226HKD, considered cheap for a dinner in a restaurant in a shopping mall. I had the Angus Beef set, it was great, I didn't expect this quality for this price. 
However the table was not very clean when I arrive, and they do not accept card when I pay the bill, that's where I take one star off.
Overall I would recommend this restaurant and will visit again, especially they do not have a long queue on a Sunday evening.
Good food with value

result.name: 意八餐廳

reviews.text: 如果你住黃大仙又鍾意飲咖啡既朋友，唯一推薦就系喺南館既意八餐廳！至於食物品質，早午晚都咁多人幫襯，就G吾差啦！ 仲有一個我鍾意佢嘅原因，係班員工好有合作精神，唔會話睇住你做我吾洗做咁，個個都好勤力！喺果食野正能量都多D呀！
我以前喺度叫咗碟牛柳絲炒麵，食咗两啖發現裏面有一條長鋼絲，好在冇吞落去咋，吞咗就大件事喇，要小心。

Food was decent, service was decent and portions were pretty filling but nothing too special. Toast was a bit too dry. Afternoon tea was a lot better, the food had good flavours and the portions were pretty big.

食品有水準，價錢合理。
食物款式無乜轉變。
